# Implementation Plan — Spec-Compliant SSE Library (Nim, stdlib only)

This is the live, workable plan for a spec-compliant Server-Sent Events library in Nim using
**only the standard library**. It is designed to be built **bottom-up, layer by layer**,
where every layer is fully tested against the spec before the next
layer begins. If a layer's exit criteria are met, we never have to revisit it.

## Notable constraints

- **Stdlib only.** No third-party packages.
- **No `std/httpclient` / `std/asynchttpclient`.** HTTP is done by hand over sockets.
- **UTF-8 only for Event streams.** Event streams **MUST** always be encoded as **UTF-8**.
- **TLS is in v1** (`https://`), implemented via `std/net` + OpenSSL (`-d:ssl`).
- **Event delivery is via callbacks** (`onOpen`, `onEvent`, `onError`).

## Notable decisions

| Decision | Choice | Rationale |
|---|---|---|
| TLS | In v1, OpenSSL via `-d:ssl` | Real endpoints are `https`. |
| Delivery | Callbacks | Maps directly to the spec's event model + delivery guard. |
| Parser I/O | None (pure) | Transport-agnostic core, exhaustively testable. |
| `retry` surfacing | Parser state, client polls | Parser owns "reconnection time" (spec §4.4); client owns reconnect policy. |
| Cancellation (async) | Cooperative flag + socket close | `await recv` unblocks naturally. |
| Cancellation (sync) | Read timeout + flag poll | Blocking `recv` can't see a flag; wake periodically. |
| Heartbeat | Server emits `: keepalive` ~15s; client has optional stall timeout | Spec §9.1 is server-side; client stall detection is the practical dual. |

## Directory Layout

```
src/
  sse.nim # umbrella; re-exports public API
  sse/
    types.nim
    parser.nim
    writer.nim
    http.nim
    client_async.nim
